```

## Database quick ref

### PostgreSQL (server)

```sql
-- team_folders: id, name, sort_order, is_deleted, local_id, created_at, updated_at
-- teams:        id, folder_id(FK→folders SET NULL), name, format_label, sort_order, is_deleted, local_id, created_at, updated_at
-- team_slots:   id, team_id(FK CASCADE), slot_index(0-5), species_id, form_name,
--               nickname(max 12), level(1-100), gender, is_shiny, ability_name,
--               nature_name, held_item_name, friendship(0-255), move_1..4,
--               ev_hp/atk/def/spa/spd/spe(0-252, total≤510), iv_hp..spe(0-31 default 31),
--               updated_at, is_deleted
```

### Drift additions (local only)

```text
-- sync_status TEXT on all server-mirrored tables: 'synced'|'pending'|'error'
-- pending_sync_ops: id, op_type, entity_type, entity_local_id, payload(JSON),
--                   created_at, retry_count(give up at 10), last_error
-- meta: key TEXT PK, value TEXT  (stores: last_pull_timestamp, device_id)
```

## Sync engine rules

1. Local write → insert `pending_sync_ops` → set `sync_status = 'pending'`
2. Sync triggers: app foreground, connectivity restored, pull-to-refresh, background every 15min
3. Process ops FIFO → on 2xx: delete op, set `sync_status = 'synced'`
4. On failure: `retry_count++`. At 10 → `sync_status = 'error'`, show badge on team card
5. After push: `GET /sync/pull?since=<last_pull_timestamp>` → merge (last-write-wins on `updated_at`)

## API endpoints (all require `X-API-Key` header)

```text
GET|POST|PATCH|DELETE  /folders
PATCH                  /folders/reorder
GET|POST               /teams         (GET accepts ?folder_id=)
GET|PATCH|DELETE       /teams/:id
POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE  /teams/:id/slots/:sid
PATCH                  /teams/:id/reorder
POST                   /sync/push     (batch ops array)
GET                    /sync/pull?since=<ISO8601>
```

